<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8ee2e833-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s290l–3"><num value="290l–3">§ 290l–3.</num><heading> Federal Reserve banks as depositories</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any Federal Reserve Bank <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002038">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002038"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should not be capitalized.</note> which is requested to do so by the Bank may act as its depository, or as its fiscal agent, and the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System shall exercise general supervision over the carrying out of these functions.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id8ee2e834-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/513/tV/s562/c/5">Pub. L. 101–513, title V, § 562(c)(5)</ref>, <date date="1990-11-05">Nov. 5, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/2034">104 Stat. 2034</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id8ee2e835-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id8ee2e836-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id8ee2e837-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Another <ref href="/us/pl/101/513/s562/c/5">section 562(c)(5) of Pub. L. 101–513</ref> is set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s2293">section 2293 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
